{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"50b051c9-e5b4-4282-bbed-f7bf3a04a519","content":"Two things changed with xUnit v3 + MTP:\n\n### 1. Filter syntax changed\nMTP doesn't use VSTest's `--filter` syntax. It uses `--filter` but with a **different expression language**. The `&` operator becomes `&` or you use parentheses, and `~` (contains) becomes a method-style syntax.\n\nYour old filter:\n```\ndotnet test --filter \"FullyQualifiedName~IntegrationTests&Category=Smoke\"\n```\n\nNew MTP equivalent:\n```\ndotnet test --filter \"FullyQualifiedName~IntegrationTests and Category=Smoke\"\n```\n\nKey differences:\n- **`&`** → **`and`** (logical AND)\n- **`|`** → **`or`** (logical OR)\n- `~` (contains), `=` (equals) still work for property matching\n\n### 2. Trait attribute changed\nIn xUnit v3, `[Trait]` is replaced by a strongly-typed `[Category]` attribute (among others). Update your test class:\n\n```diff\n- [Trait(\"Category\", \"Smoke\")]\n+ [Category(\"Smoke\")]\n```\n\nThis matters because MTP maps `[Category(\"Smoke\")]` to the `Category` filter property natively.\n\n### Summary\n\n| Aspect | v2 + VSTest | v3 + MTP |\n|--------|-------------|----------|\n| Attribute | `[Trait(\"Category\",\"Smoke\")]` | `[Category(\"Smoke\")]` |\n| CI filter | `--filter \"...&...\"` | `--filter \"... and ...\"` |\n\nWant me to apply these changes to your files?","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"591d65dd-91db-414a-92b1-2d8c401a4089","outputTokens":395,"requestId":"982B:3AB79D:190318:209A59:69FFD8EC"},"id":"76eb59dc-a605-48b8-83c1-d53fbb4ebc38","timestamp":"2026-05-10T01:01:44.961Z","parentId":"2380ad83-fc52-4313-a158-2c66024a6442"}
